fields.Title: WHIRLING F2 / TEQUILA DOOR
fields.Description: The dialogue between you and the door to your room. It is locked unless you've paid for damages.

fields.Title: You: ""Aaaaa! It huuurts!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aaaaa! It huuurts!"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Nice try. The tears come streaming..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nice try. The tears come streaming down your face as you crumble to the ground.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The tears bring some relief, but no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tears bring some relief, but not much.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He nods toward the staircase. "Come..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods toward the staircase. "Come on, let's go down."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It must be an electronic lock. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It must be an electronic lock. You will have to get Garte, the cafeteria manager, to open it first -- after you've paid for the night."

fields.Title: You: "Blubber. And keep blubbering."
fields.Dialogue Text: Blubber. And keep blubbering.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Just a moment. We should talk abou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just a moment. We should talk about our progress on the investigation. Let's go out to the balcony."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: "(His voice echoes from downstairs.)..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (His voice echoes from downstairs.) "What the hell is going on up there?"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You could try climbing into that tr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could try climbing into that trash bin in the yard, hobocop style... after you've gotten open the lid.

fields.Title: You: "Try to unlock the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try to unlock the door.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I would advise against that. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I would advise against that. It's already late, and you won't find cheaper accommodation in the vicinity."

fields.Title: Authority: "He's asserting his leadership talen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's asserting his leadership talents because he is concerned about you.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Your angry voice carries through th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your angry voice carries through the Whirling, but you still can't stop the tears from welling up in your eyes...

fields.Title: You: ""This door will fall prostrate befo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This door will fall prostrate before The Law!" (Punch the door again.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant purses his lips. "Ad..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant purses his lips. "Admirable form. Now come on, let's go down."

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "The door rings from the impact, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door rings from the impact, but does not budge.

fields.Title: You: ""Nah, I'll get by somehow. Didn't l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, I'll get by somehow. Didn't like that room very much anyway."

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "This is the door to your room."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is the door to your room.
fields.Alternate1: This is the door to the room you *redecorated*.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: "(His voice echoes from downstairs.)..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (His voice echoes from downstairs.) "What's going on up there?"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Pow-pow! That was impressive."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pow-pow! That was impressive.

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "The door shudders, but appears unda..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door shudders, but appears undamaged.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You could try climbing into that tr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could try climbing into that trash bin in the yard, hobocop style...

fields.Title: Volition: "You feel uncertain, like a child wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You feel uncertain, like a child who's lost his mother in the crowd.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Because it's your last lifeline to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because it's your last lifeline to being a police officer instead of a hobo.

fields.Title: Composure: "You've got this. Men like you don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've got this. Men like you don't cry unless it serves their purposes.

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, let's go.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, let's go."

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "Your key no longer turns in the loc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your key no longer turns in the lock.

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, I don't need to pay -- I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, I don't need to pay -- I will brave the streets. Go undercover as a hobocop."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks on impassively..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks on impassively. "Even if you could break down the door, all you would get is another bill."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: "(His voice echoes from downstairs.)..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (His voice echoes from downstairs.) "What's going on up there?"

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "The door appears undamaged, and eve..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door appears undamaged, and even more impassive than the lieutenant.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Yes, and it's not just a matter of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, and it's not just a matter of comfort, but also of principle. This may be your last lifeline to being a police officer instead of a hobo.

fields.Title: You: ""Good night, lieutenant.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good night, lieutenant."

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "The door to your room locks every n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door to your room locks every night at 21.00 if you haven't paid for the room. You can pay downstairs when speaking to Garte, the cafeteria manager.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He nods. "Yes, we both need to get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods. "Yes, we both need to get proper rest tonight."

fields.Title: You: "Observe the damage to your knuckles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Observe the damage to your knuckles. Is this really worth it?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Just a moment. You had some questi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just a moment. You had some questions earlier, I believe, and, besides, we should discuss our progress on the investigation. Let's go out to the balcony."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Hey, remember that trash bin idea....."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hey, remember that trash bin idea...? Time to get climbing!

fields.Title: You: "Still sounds better than sleeping o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still sounds better than sleeping outside.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Just punch the damned door. No *loc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just punch the damned door. No *locks* are going to keep you out.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Our investigation does not at pres..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our investigation does not at present require for anyone to go undercover. Let's drop this discussion and go settle your debt with the manager."

fields.Title: You: "Try to stay cool."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try to stay cool.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "It hurts, but keep your cool. You'v..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It hurts, but keep your cool. You've got this.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: "(His voice echoes from downstairs.)..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (His voice echoes from downstairs.) "What the hell is going on up there?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at you with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at you with a mixture of pity and weariness. "Come on, let's go down."

fields.Title: You: "Why would I want to stay in such a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why would I want to stay in such a place?

fields.Title: You: ""Right, I should go pay my debts be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right, I should go pay my debts before I can go to sleep."

fields.Title: You: "Punch the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Punch the door.

fields.Title: Door, Room #1: "Something about it has changed."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something about it has changed.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "*Even if you could*? Don't let him..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Even if you could*? Don't let him talk you down, son!

fields.Title: You: "Try one more time. This time with b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try one more time. This time with both fists, one after the other.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at you with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at you with a mixture of pity and weariness. "Come on, let's go down."

fields.Title: You: "Keep it in. Cradle your arm."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep it in. Cradle your arm.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Your fist bounces off the door and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your fist bounces off the door and comes back to you on a wave of agony that surges up your arm.

fields.Title: You: "Confront the door with a stoical ex..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Confront the door with a stoical expression. You are still The Law.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: "The air outside is brisk, the lieut..."]
